11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 2104, as
13 last amended by Section 1, Chapter 252, O.S.L. 2025 (68 O.S. Supp.
14 2024, Section 2104), is amended to read as follows:
15 Section 2104. A. The value of any motor vehicle, except a
16 manufactured home, for the purposes of the excise tax levied by
17 Section 2103 of this title, shall be determined as of the time the
18 person applying for a certificate of title thereto obtained either
19 ownership or possession of the vehicle, which shall be presumed to
20 be the actual date of the sale or other transfer of ownership, and
21 assignment of the certificate of title.
22 B. The value of any vehicle, for purposes of the excise tax
23 levied by Section 2103 of this title, shall be the actual sales
24 price of such a vehicle after reducing the sales price by any
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2952 Page 1

1 cred its or discounts given for a trade-in vehicle, if a trade-in was
2 made as part of the transaction. The actual sales price of the
3 vehicle, which total shall be the basis of the motor vehicle excise
4 tax, as well as the number of tires on the vehicle and the tire rim
5 diameters, shall be entered on the bill of sale furnished by the
6 seller to the purchaser, or on such other form as may be prescribed
7 by Service Oklahoma.
8 Upon receipt of the properly completed bill of sale or other
9 form as prescribed by Service Oklahoma, and the payment of all
10 applicable taxes and fees, Service Oklahoma or an appointed licensed
11 operator shall issue a vehicle certificate of title in accordance
12 with the provisions of the Oklahoma Vehicle License and Registration
13 Act.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
15 Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
